Who pays for the gas if you're a mortgage field inspector?

If you're a mortgage field inspector, you typically cover your own gas and travel expenses. These costs are usually factored into the fees you charge for each inspection. In other words, you're generally considered an independent contractor and manage your own expenses related to the job.
